{
  "text": "The assumption of exchangeability is only of technical nature and, if we consider P as a randomized point set, may be always obtained in the process of symmetrization. Indeed, letP be a point set such that everyp ∈P is uniformly distributed in [0, [CITATION_1] d and let π be a random uniformly chosen permutation of [N] . Then (p π(1) , . . . ,p π(N ) ) is already a sampling scheme.",
